The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Gavaskar   heads jury
                                                   Gavaskar   heads jury
            A STAFF REPORTER                            
	Calcutta: Legendary Sunil Gavaskar has been named chairman of the jury for the Sahara Indian Sports Award. The Sports Journalist Federation of India (SJFI) will nominate the sportspersons for the awards in different categories.         
	The other jury members include Michael Ferreira (billiards), Pullela Gopichand (badminton), Ashwini Nachappa (athletics), Nandan Bal (tennis), Mehrwan Daruwalla (squash), Praveen Thipsay (chess), Dhanraj Pillai (hockey), Kamlesh Mehta (table tennis), Dilip Vengsarkar (cricket), Anju Bobby George (athletics), Vikramjit Singh (golf) and I.M. Vijayan (football).                                                                                                                       
